The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Varca, Feb. 26 (PTI): The National Commission for Women has recommended changes in the definition of rape in the proposed sexual assault bill to include assaults other than penetration.

 We have submitted the sexual assault bill to the government. In that, we have changed the definition of rape. We call it sexual assault, NCW chairperson Girija Vyas said in Goa today. 

 New Delhi (PTI): People can now book a ticket through the railways passenger reservation system for the Samjhauta Express in eight railway stations on all days. Pakistan-bound passengers with valid visa and passport can now have reservation up to 15 days in advance.

 Phulbani (PTI): Seven persons were killed when a bus fell off a hilly road in Orissas Kalingaghat on Monday. The Berhampur-bound bus with 55 passengers on board, crashed through the concrete barricade and got stuck on a tree about 100 feet below. 

 Jammu (PTI): Over 4,000 stranded passengers crossed over a 300-metre stretch on the Jammu-Srinagar national highway by foot as the damaged road remained closed for the seventh day on Monday. Inclement weather had hit the restoration work.

 Sonepat (PTI): A student has been electrocuted while watching cricket match in Sonepat, Haryana. The engineering student came in touch with a high-tension wire while watching some boys playing cricket from his hostel roof on Sunday.

 Akola: (PTI): Two farmers hanged themselves in Maharashtras Akola on Sunday allegedly under pressure from mounting debt, police said.




